rise system required manual copying of Client IDs and secrets. DCR eliminates this by allowing Gemini Enterprise to programmatically register itself as an OAuth client with your agent's authorization server. How the DCR Flow Works: Discovery: The Gemini Enterprise app reads your Agent Card to find the DCR endpoint. Request: Google sends an HTTP POST to your endpoint containing a software_statement which is a cryptographically signed JSON Web Token (JWT). Validation: Your backend verifies the JWT signature using Google's public keys to ensure the request is authentic. Provisioning: Upon success, your server creates a new OpenID Connect (OIDC) application in your identity provider (e.g., Okta) and returns the client_id and client_secret to Gemini Enterprise. code_block <ListValue: [StructValue([('code', 'DCR Request
